summary:
The Security Council,

Reaffirming its determination to combat impunity for international crimes and ensure that all persons indicted by the International Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia (ICTY) are brought to justice,

Recalling previous resolutions on the ICTY, 

Reiterates its request to the ICTY to complete its work expeditiously, aiming to transition to the International Residual Mechanism for Criminal Tribunals; 

Takes note of the ICTY's commitment to complete its judicial work by 30 November 2017; 

Extends the terms of office of permanent judges until 30 November 2017 or until completion of assigned cases; 

Reappoints Mr. Serge Brammertz as Prosecutor for a term until 30 November 2017; 

Extends Judge Carmel Agius's term as President of the ICTY until 31 December 2017; 

Urges States to cooperate fully with the ICTY and the Mechanism; 

Commends the Office of Internal Oversight Services' evaluation and encourages the ICTY to report on implementation; 

Welcomes the adoption of the "Code of Professional Conduct for the Judges of the Tribunal"; 

Decides to remain seized of the matter.
